TY  - JOUR
AU  - Goldstein, Itay
AU  - Ozdenoren, Emre
AU  - Yuan, Kathy
T1  - Learning and Complementarities in Speculative Attacks
PY  - 2011
Y1  - 2011/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdq017
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 78
IS  - 1
SP  - 263
EP  - 292
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We study a model where the aggregate trading of currency speculators reveals new information to the central bank and affects its policy decision. We show that the learning process gives rise to coordination motives among speculators leading to large currency attacks and introducing non-fundamental volatility into exchange rates and policy decisions. We show that the central bank can improve the ex ante effectiveness of its policy by committing to put a lower weight ex post on the information from the market, and that transparency may either increase or decrease the effectiveness of learning from the market, depending on how it is implemented.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdq017
ER  - 



